 Scenario:
 On a custom Order__c object, the Tracking_ID__c is stored. Users
 want to click a button that fetches live tracking info from a
 courier API and displays it in a modal (Lightning component).
 Question: How would you fetch live data from an external API
 when a button is clicked on a Salesforce record page?
 âœ…
 Answer:
 This is where Apex + Lightning Component + API
 callout come together. I would create an Apex
 controller that performs the callout using the orderâ€™s
 tracking ID. The Lightning component calls this
 method when the user clicks a button.
 ðŸ”„
 Lightning Flow:
 Lead Inserted â†’ Trigger calls future method
 Future method sends address to API
 API responds with corrected address â†’ we update the
 Lead
 apex
 public with sharing class TrackingController {
 @AuraEnabled(cacheable=false)
 public static String getTrackingStatus(String trackingId) {
 HttpRequest req = new HttpRequest();
 req.setEndpoint('https://api.shiptrack.com/track?tracking_id=' + trackingId);
 req.setMethod('GET');
 Http http = new Http();
 HttpResponse res = http.send(req);
 if (res.getStatusCode() == 200) {
 Map<String, Object> result = (Map<String, Object>)
 JSON.deserializeUntyped(res.getBody());
 return String.valueOf(result.get('current_status'));
 } else {
 return 'Unable to fetch status';
 }
 }
 }
