 Scenario:
 Your company uses an external HRMS system that exposes
 employee data via OAuth 2.0. Your task is to integrate it with
 Salesforce to fetch employee records once daily.
 Question: How would you implement OAuth 2.0 flow in Salesforce
 to call a protected external API?
 âœ…
 Answer:
 use Named Credentials with OAuth 2.0 â€” this is the
 most secure and Salesforce-recommended
 approach. Once the admin completes the OAuth
 handshake, the access token is managed by
 Salesforce.
 ðŸ”‘
 Setup Steps:
 1.Create Auth Provider in Salesforce with client ID, secret,
 and callback URL
 2.Create Named Credential linked to the Auth Provider
 3.Use that Named Credential in your code
 
Your next opportunity is closer than you think. Letâ€™s get you there!
 ðŸ“ž
 Donâ€™t waitâ€”call us at +91 98604 38743 today
 apex
 public class HRMSIntegrationJob implements Schedulable {
    public void execute(SchedulableContext sc) {
        HttpRequest req = new HttpRequest();
        req.setEndpoint('callout:HRMS_Named_Credential/api/employees');
        req.setMethod('GET');
        Http http = new Http();
        HttpResponse res = http.send(req);
        if (res.getStatusCode() == 200) {
            List<Map<String, Object>> employees = (List<Map<String, Object>>)
 JSON.deserializeUntyped(res.getBody());
            for (Map<String, Object> emp : employees) {
                System.debug('Employee: ' + emp.get('name'));
            }
        } else {
            System.debug('Failed to fetch employees: ' + res.getBody());
        }
    }
 }
