 Scenario:
 Your Salesforce org needs to notify a downstream inventory
 management system whenever an Opportunity is Closed-Won,
 sending the list of products in that opportunity.
 Question: How would you design a scalable, loosely-coupled
 integration using Platform Events?
 âœ…
 Answer:
 Platform Event called OpportunityWonEvent__e with
 opportunity ID and product info. The downstream system can
 subscribe to it via CometD client or Mulesoft.
 This decouples the systems â€” Salesforce just publishes an
 event and forgets.
 ðŸ“œ
 Steps:
 1.Define OpportunityWonEvent__e custom platform event
 2.Trigger on Opportunity â†’ on Closed-Won â†’ publish event
 3.External system subscribes to the event via streaming
 
Your next opportunity is closer than you think. Letâ€™s get you there!
 ðŸ“ž
 Donâ€™t waitâ€”call us at +91 98604 38743 today
 apex
 trigger OpportunityWinEventTrigger on Opportunity (after update) {
    List<OpportunityWonEvent__e> eventsToPublish = new List<OpportunityWonEvent__e>();
    for (Opportunity opp : Trigger.new) {
        Opportunity old = Trigger.oldMap.get(opp.Id);
        if (opp.StageName == 'Closed Won' && old.StageName != 'Closed Won') {
            String productList = ''; 
            for (OpportunityLineItem oli : [SELECT Product2.Name FROM OpportunityLineItem
 WHERE OpportunityId = :opp.Id]) {
                productList += oli.Product2.Name + '; ';
            }
            OpportunityWonEvent__e evt = new OpportunityWonEvent__e(
                OpportunityId__c = opp.Id,
                ProductList__c = productList
            );
            eventsToPublish.add(evt);
        }
    }
    if (!eventsToPublish.isEmpty()) {
        EventBus.publish(eventsToPublish);
    }
 }
