 Scenario:
 After the warehouse updates an external system that an
 order has shipped, Salesforce should receive this information
 and update the Fulfillment_Status__c field on Order__c.
 Question: How would you leverage Platform Events to receive
 order fulfillment events from an external system?
 âœ…
 Answer:
 define a Platform Eventâ€”OrderFulfilledEvent__eâ€”with relevant
 fields (OrderNumber, FulfillmentStatus).
 The external system (via middleware) publishes this event.
 Salesforce subscribes to it via an Apex trigger and updates
 the corresponding Order.
 ðŸ“œ
 Logic:
 1.Platform Events are great for decoupled, event-driven
 integrations. Salesforce doesnâ€™t query external systems
 repeatedlyâ€”instead, it reacts to events raised by the
 warehouse system.
 
