 Scenario:
 Your client must submit invoicing data to a government portal
 secured via JWT bearer token. Salesforce needs to generate the
 JWT using a private key, call the token endpoint to receive the
 access token, then send the invoice.
 Question: How would you implement a JWTâ€‘based authentication
 flow using Apex to call a government API?
 âœ…
 Answer:
 Generating and sending JWTs in Apex takes care â€” I build the
 header and claim, sign it using Crypto.sign, and then use that
 JWT in the token endpoint call. Once the access token is
 received, I send the invoice payload.
 
Your next opportunity is closer than you think. Letâ€™s get you there!
 ðŸ“ž
 Donâ€™t waitâ€”call us at +91 98604 38743 today
 apex
 public class GovtJwtService {
    public static String getAccessToken() {
        String header = '{"alg":"RS256","typ":"JWT"}';
        Map<String, Object> claimMap = new Map<String, Object>{
            'iss' => 'YourClientID',
            'aud' => 'https://gov.api/token',
            'exp' => (Datetime.now().getTime()/1000) + 300
        };
        String claim = JSON.serialize(claimMap);
        String jwt = EncodingUtil.base64Encode(Blob.valueOf(header)) + '.' +
                     EncodingUtil.base64Encode(Blob.valueOf(claim));
        Blob privateKey = Blob.valueOf('-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----...');
        Blob sig = Crypto.sign('RSA-SHA256', Blob.valueOf(jwt), privateKey);
        jwt += '.' + EncodingUtil.base64Encode(sig);
        HttpRequest req = new HttpRequest();
        req.setEndpoint('https://gov.api/token');
        req.setMethod('POST');
        req.setHeader('Content-Type', 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded');
        req.setBody('grant_type=client_credentials&assertion=' + jwt);
        HttpResponse res = new Http().send(req);
        Map<String,Object> resp = (Map<String,Object>)
 JSON.deserializeUntyped(res.getBody());
        return (String)resp.get('access_token');
    }
 }
